      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PHOENIX VIOLET (2) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close second, a nose from the winner WEST END LASS (23.11) at this track. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Overdue and expected to feature again. WEST END LASS (5) goes very well this course and distance starting 16 times for seven wins and five minors. Comes off a (23.10) win last time, scoring by a nose in a Grade 4/5 over 400m at this track. Looks a key chance on best figures. ZIPPING TAMIKA (1) was safely held in tougher company last start at Healesville, but prior to that won by a neck at Shepparton (25.77) beating Paw Manny in a Rank Limit - Grade 5 on May 14. Form from her last run is proving strong. Has ability and can measure up. SHIFTY BULLDOZER (3) generally performs well over this distance.",
